  "text": "The very abrupt transition or flip-flop between two highly contrasted c-axis fabric patterns at around 700 m at Siple Dome not only reflects an abrupt change in the nature of the stress-strain field, it also signals a major change in the rheological properties of the ice. No such abrupt change in texture or fabric has been observed in cores from other ice dome sites, for example, Dome F (Azuma and others, 1999) or Dome C (Wang and others, 2003) in East Antarctica where the ice is approximately three times thicker than at Siple Dome. The potential importance of widespread incorporation of volcanic particles on the rheological properties of ice from 700-800 m at Siple Dome is discussed in greater detail by [CITATION_1] .",
